EXECUTIVE CHEF
-
DUB001493
Description
You will be responsible for the efficient profitable running of the Culinary Department in line with Hyatt International's Corporate Strategies and brand standards, whilst meeting employee, guest and owner expectations. The Executive Chef is responsible to manage the full Food and Beverage Culinary facilities of Grand Hyatt Dubai with multiple kitchens servicing 14 Food and Beverage outlets and 5,000 sq mtrs of function space and extensive outdoor catering to multiple venues within the hotel grounds. You will be responsible for leading a large Team of professionals operating to Hyatt International standards, ensuring maximum guest satisfaction while operating within budget, helping to ensure the financial success of the operation.
Qualifications
Qualifications
Minimum of 5 years’ experience as an Executive Chef in large luxury international branded hotels.
Extensive experience in large conference and events operations.
Proven leadership of a large kitchen brigade
Working knowledge of kitchen hygiene practices and occupational health and safety standards will be essential.
Computer Skills in MS Office and Outlook as well as working knowledge of Scala and Hyperion
